        <h1>LeetCode 3838: Weighted Word Mapping (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                You are given a list of words and a weight array where weights[i] represents the weight of character
                ('a' + i). For each word, calculate the sum of weights of all characters in that word. Map this sum to a
                character using the formula: character = 'z' - (sum % 26). Return the resulting string of mapped
                characters.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: words = ["aabcb","cd"], weights =
                [15,10,20,25,-20,15,-25,10,0,0,0,10,0,-5,0,-5,0,0,20,10,0,0,0,0,-5,0]<br>
                Output: "mxz"<br>
                Explanation: For "aabcb": weight = 15+15+10+20+10 = 70, 70%26=18, 'z'-18='h'. For "cd": weight =
                25+(-20) = 5, 5%26=5, 'z'-5='u'. And so on.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    string mapWordWeights(vector&lt;string&gt;&amp; words, vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; weights) {
        string res;
        for (auto str : words) {
            int wt = 0;
            // Add weights of all characters in the word
            for (char c : str) {
                wt += weights[c - 'a'];
            }
            wt %= 26;
            res.push_back('z' - wt);
        }
        return res;
    }
};</code></pre>
